      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Allowing yourself to surrender to this overwhelming silence can be a paradoxically liberating experience. Allowing the space to be empty, without trying to fill it with memories or distractions, may be the simplest way to come to terms with what's been lost. It's almost as if letting go of trying to hold on to the past can be a small, incremental step towards healing.",
      "source": "target",
